          "SAMPLE": [
            {
              "pointer": "",
              "coded_information": null,
              "free_text": [
                "Eight samples of natural uranium, irradiated over an",
                "exposure of 300-1,600 MWd/ton. The samples were derived",
                "from experimental rods of uranium irradiated in a",
                "heavy-water-moderated and -cooled Savannah River",
                "production reactor. Samples were sectioned from each",
                "rod, dissolved and analyzed for tritium content.",
                "Sections weighing 40-80 g were cut from each rod, and",
                "any adherent film of tritiated deuterium oxide removed",
                "with a solution of sodium hydroxide. The uranium of",
                "each section was then dissolved in nitric acid an",
                "apparatus designed to collect the off-gas",
                "quantitatively. The collected gas was scrubbed to",
                "remove nitrogen oxides and then was passed through",
                "copper oxide combustion tube to convert any hydrogen to",
                "water."
              ]
            }
          ],
